Each of the Programs above may result in recommendations ranging from capital improvements to routine maintenance of the plant.  Work Orders are established where necessary.  Current planned changes to improve safety are the result of the most recent PHA performed in January 2009, which resulted in 25 recommendations.  Many of the recommendations were completed or in the process of implementation as of the date of this RMP filing.  A summary of the recommendations includes additional evaluation and/or improvement of administrative, engineering, electrical, mechanical, and seismic issues.  The actual recommendations include:  Policy letter to Contractors; Validation of Technician qualifications for seasonal set-up and tear-down; Development of written policy regarding rental equipment and its maintenance; Seasonal shutdown SOP's to be reviewed for avoidance of trapping liquid ammonia; Consult with vendor about the capabilities of the Lookout system and training appropriate personnel; Consider loading a clone of the Lookout program on the Maintenance Supervisor's laptop (temp backup); Switch to less aggressive scale control product (contact Condenser treatment vendor); Install valve plugs and bracing as shown at walk-through; Verify that pipe labeling and color coding is adequate with emphasis on Engine room area-include refresher training for Maintenance Department; Verify compressor SOPA?s adequately address Emergency Shutdown including safety measures and PPEA?provide refresher training as needed; Check with insurance co. for providing infrared check of electrical panels (Thermo-grap
